Appendix A: Mathematical Foundations

A.1 Quantum Information Theory

```
Key Equations:
- Quantum state: |ψ⟩ = α|0⟩ + β|1⟩
- Density matrix: ρ = ∑ p_i|ψ_i⟩⟨ψ_i|
- Quantum entropy: S(ρ) = -Tr(ρ log ρ)
```

A.2 Type-2 Fuzzy Logic

```
Formal Definitions:
- Type-2 fuzzy set: Ã = ∫∫ μ_Ã(x,u)/(x,u)
- Footprint of uncertainty: FOU(Ã) = ∪∀x∈X J_x
- Embedded type-1 sets: A_e = ∫ μ_A_e(x)/x
```

Appendix B: Security Proofs

B.1 Zero-Trust Security Theorems

```
Theorem 1 (Continuous Verification):
For any session S, the probability of undetected compromise after time t is bounded by:
P(compromise) ≤ e^{-λt}
Where λ is the verification rate.

Theorem 2 (Quantum Resistance):
All cryptographic operations remain secure against quantum adversaries with polynomial-time quantum algorithms.
```

